  "text": "There is abundant clinical evidence in international literature supporting the efficacy of biophysical stimulation on nonunion fractures, particularly with PEMFs; authors have reported success rates of around 70-80% [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] (Table 3) . Good results have also been obtained in the treatment of non-union fractures with CCEFs and with LIPUS, albeit on a lesser scale.",
